<TITLE> Buddhists celebrating Buddha Purnima </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 27 (bdnews24.com)  Buddhist people across the country are celebrating Buddha Purnima, the biggest annual religious festival for the community, on Thursday with a host of programmes. The birth of the religion's founder Gautam Buddha, his attainment of perfect knowledge and death is believed by buddhists to have occurred in the full moon of Baishakh. Buddha is said to have appeared on earth on this day about 2,553 years ago. The day is being commemorated through peace processions, prayers and distribution of offerings. Similar events are taking place elsewhere in the world. President Zillur Rahman, prime minister Sheikh Hasina and opposition leader Khaleda Zia in separate messages greeted the Buddhists on the occasion. Leaders of different social, political and cultural organisations sent messages. Bangladesh Buddhist Federation is holding the main programme at International Buddha Bihar at Merul Badda. Prorgramme will begin with the burning of Mangal Pradip. Other rituals like Buddha Puja (worship), Mahasangadan, Maha Astapariskardan will take place later on in the day. Special prayers will be offered wishing peace and prosperity of all living beings on earth. Bangladesh Buddha Sangskritik Parisad brought out a procession at around 8am from Shahbagh. The president is expected to exchange greetings with the Buddhist community at the Bangabhaban later in the day. Thursday is a public holiday on the occasion of Buddha Purnima. bdnews24.
